Sympathisers of 22-year-old Bamise Ayanwole, who went missing after boarding a Bus Rapid Transport (BRT) service on February 26, have protested her gruesome murder. Bamise, who went missing on Saturday February 26, was found dead on Monday. The Police subsequently arrested the driver, Nice Andrew Omininikoron, on the same day.   Osun PDP holds parallel governorship primaries     What to know about International Women’s Day (IWD)     PHOTOS: Distraught mother demands justice for slain BRT…   Ayanwola got missing while returning to Otta from Ajah when she boarded a BRT bus with number 240257 going to Oshodi at about 7 pm at Chevron Bus Stop. The sympathisers gathered at Bamise’s residence to condole with the family. They called on Lagos Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu and the Commissioner of Police to ensure justice is served.